title.narrative: Provision of expert engineering/infrastructure programme management, social analysis, results, climate change and legal advice to the Caribbean Development Bank.

description.narrative: This activity (Provision of expert engineering/infrastructure programme management, social analysis, results, climate change and legal advice to the Caribbean Development Bank.) is a component of UK Caribbean Infrastructure Fund reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Multilateral organisation' and a budget of £3,220,546. This component benefits West Indies, regional, and works in the following sector(s): Water supply and sanitation - large systems, Transport policy and administrative management, Road transport, Energy generation, renewable sources - multiple technologies, Agricultural land resources, Flood prevention/control. The start date is 29-01-2016 and the end date is 31-03-2024.
